# pulsar-dmypy

Incremental MyPy integration for Pulsar using `dmypy`.

Created by iFA.  
Initial implementation was AI-assisted and refined manually.

## ⚠ Platform Support

Currently **Linux-only**.

The plugin relies on filesystem symlinks for the shadow project system.  
Windows is not supported (unless using WSL).

macOS may work but is not officially tested.

## Features

- Uses `dmypy` daemon for fast incremental type checking
- Shadow project overlay (symlink-based)
- Supports unsaved buffers
- Real-time linting with debounce
- Only shows errors for the active file
- Fully integrated with Pulsar Linter API

## Requirements

- Python 3
- `mypy`
- `dmypy` available in PATH
- Pulsar Linter package installed
- Linux filesystem with symlink support

## How It Works

The plugin creates a shadow project directory:
.pulsar_dmypy_cache


Inside this directory:

- All Python files are symlinked
- Open editors are written with in-memory content
- `dmypy run` executes inside the shadow project

This allows:

- Full project type checking
- Unsaved buffer support
- Incremental performance

## Limitations

- Full shadow tree rebuild on each lint (optimized for small projects)
- Linux-only due to symlink dependency

